UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 79
1 AN ACT relating to video teleconference meetings.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 Section 1. KRS 12.070 is amended to read as follows:
4 (1) For the purpose of this section, "minority" means American Indian; Alaskan native;
5 African-American; Hispanic, including persons of Mexican, Puerto Rican, Cuban,
6 and Central or South American origin; Pacific islander; or other ethnic group
7 underrepresented on state boards and commissions.
8 (2) Except as otherwise expressly provided by law, the members of each administrative
9 board or commission shall be citizens of Kentucky appointed by the Governor from
10 the state at large on the basis of their interests in public affairs, their good judgment,
11 and their knowledge and ability in the field of action of the department for which
12 appointed, with a view to providing diversity of interests and points of view in the
13 membership and without regard to their political or religious opinions or
14 affiliations.
15 (3) Where appointments to administrative boards and commissions are made from lists
16 submitted to him or her, the Governor may reject the list and require that other lists
17 be submitted. Notwithstanding any provision to the contrary, in the event the
18 current membership of a board or commission reflects a proportion of the minority
19 group less than the proportion of the minority group in the total population of the
20 Commonwealth, then the Governor may appoint a member of the minority group
21 even if the list of nominees for a vacancy does not include a member of the
22 minority group.
23 (4) Before entering upon the duties of their office, all members of administrative
24 boards and commissions shall take the oath of office prescribed by Section 228 of
25 the Constitution of Kentucky.
26 (5) (a) A board, commission, or similar administrative body may conduct video
27 teleconference meetings in accordance with Section 2 of this Act to allow
Page 1 of 5
