UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 79
1 members of the public to attend and participate.
2 (b) 1. A member of a board, commission, or similar administrative body may
3 attend a meeting virtually through video teleconference unless a
4 decision of the board, commission, or similar administrative body at
5 the meeting:
6 a. Would result in an action that implements, interprets, or
7 prescribes law or policy or affects private rights or procedures
8 available to the public; or
9 b. Administers or awards funds.
10 2. Members who attend a meeting virtually through video teleconference
11 shall not receive reimbursement for travel expenses.
12 (6) When a board, commission, or similar administrative body is established and no
13 provision is made for compensation of members, members shall serve without pay,
14 but may receive reimbursement for their actual and necessary expenses.
15 Section 2. KRS 61.826 is amended to read as follows:
16 (1) A public agency may conduct any meeting through video teleconference.
17 (2) Notice of a video teleconference meeting shall:
18 (a) Comply with the requirements of KRS 61.820 or 61.823 as appropriate;
19 (b) Clearly state that the meeting will be a video teleconference;
20 (c) Provide specific information on how any member of the public or media
21 organization may view the meeting electronically; and
22 (d) In any case where the public agency has elected to provide a physical
23 location, or in any circumstance where two (2) or more members of the public
24 agency are attending a video teleconference meeting from the same physical
25 location, precisely identify a primary physical location of the video
26 teleconference where all members can be seen and heard and the public may
27 attend in accordance with KRS 61.840.
Page 2 of 5
XXXX 10/2/2025 2:44 PM Jacketed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 79
1 (3) The same procedures with regard to participation, distribution of materials, and
2 other matters shall apply in all video teleconference locations. Members of the
3 public agency who participate in a video teleconference shall remain visible on
4 camera at all times that business is being discussed.
5 (4) Any interruption in the video or audio broadcast of a video teleconference at any
6 location shall result in the suspension of the video teleconference until the broadcast
7 is restored.
8 (5) If a regular meeting is changed to a video conference, the meeting shall remain a
9 regular meeting if the meeting occurs on the same date and time as originally
10 scheduled and the public agency follows the provisions of KRS 61.823(4) to
11 provide a notice that meets the requirements of subsection (2)(b) to (d) of this
12 section.
13 (6) A member of a public agency who participates in a video teleconference meeting
14 or attends a regular meeting virtually through video teleconference shall not
15 receive reimbursement for travel expenses.
16 Section 3. KRS 164.004 is amended to read as follows:
17 (1) The Strategic Committee on Postsecondary Education is hereby created and
18 established. The committee shall be composed of members appointed by the
19 Council on Postsecondary Education, the Governor, and the General Assembly. The
20 council's representatives shall consist of the chair of the council, the president of the
21 council, and five (5) members of the council designated by the chair. The
22 Governor's representatives shall consist of the Governor and six (6) persons
23 designated by the Governor. The General Assembly's representatives shall consist
24 of the President of the Senate, the Speaker of the House of Representatives, the
25 Majority and Minority Floor Leaders of both chambers of the General Assembly,
26 the minority caucus chair of each chamber, a member appointed by the President of
27 the Senate, a member appointed by the Speaker of the House of Representatives, a
Page 3 of 5
XXXX 10/2/2025 2:44 PM Jacketed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 79
1 member appointed by the Minority Floor Leader of the Senate, a member appointed
2 by the Minority Floor Leader of the House of Representatives, and the chair of the
3 Committee on Appropriations and Revenue of each chamber.
4 (2) The chair of the council shall serve as chair of the committee. The committee shall
5 meet at least quarterly and at other times upon the written call of the chair or of
6 majorities of any two (2) of the three (3) groups that compose the committee.
7 (3) Nonlegislative members of the committee shall serve without compensation but
8 shall be reimbursed for their actual and necessary expenses, as set forth in KRS
9 12.070(5) and (6). Committee members who are Kentucky legislators shall be
10 compensated for attendance at committee meetings from the legislative branch
11 budget bill and as set forth in KRS 6.190.
12 (4) The committee shall serve as a forum for the council and the elected leadership of
13 the Commonwealth to exchange ideas about the future of postsecondary education
14 in Kentucky.
15 (5) The council shall periodically review its strategic implementation plan for the
16 strategic agenda under KRS 164.0203 and advise the committee of the actions
17 necessary to meet the goals established in KRS 164.003(2). The elected leaders
18 shall review and comment on the strategic agenda and the timetable for
19 implementation.
20 (6) The Governor shall advise the committee about the financial condition of the
21 Commonwealth and the probable funds the executive branch intends to recommend
22 to the General Assembly to be appropriated for postsecondary education.
23 (7) The legislative members shall react to the comments of the council and the
24 Governor.
25 (8) The council shall advise the committee about its opinion of how the postsecondary
26 education funds projected to be available should be allocated based on priorities and
27 projected resources. Nothing in this section shall be construed to infringe upon the
Page 4 of 5
XXXX 10/2/2025 2:44 PM Jacketed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 79
1 Governor's duty under KRS 48.100 to recommend appropriations to the General
2 Assembly or upon the General Assembly's power to make final appropriations in
3 the enacted budget.
4 (9) The committee shall have the advisory authority not explicitly prohibited by law
5 that is necessary to carry out and effectuate its advisory functions, duties, and
6 responsibilities, including the following:
7 (a) Receive reports from the council on the development and implementation of
8 the long-term strategic agenda, including biennial budget requests for
9 postsecondary education and any subsequent and related budget requests;
10 (b) Review the council's proposed objectives and benchmarks for the next fiscal
11 biennium for furthering the Commonwealth's achievement of the goals set out
12 in KRS 164.003(2);
13 (c) Consider and advise the council on the general budget parameters regarding
14 development of the postsecondary budget for the next fiscal biennium;
15 (d) Review biennial budget requests from the council for the next fiscal biennium
16 including base funding, increases in base funding, and funding for a strategic
17 investment and incentive funding program, including criteria to be used in
18 allocating these funds to institutions;
19 (e) Receive from the council, at least annually and on a more frequent basis if
20 requested by the committee, accountability reports, budget information, and
21 other information the committee deems proper; and
22 (f) Serve as the search committee for the review and consideration of candidates
23 to be presented to the council for the initial appointment to the position of
24 president of the Council on Postsecondary Education. Each group of the
25 committee shall have one (1) vote on the search committee. The vote of each
26 group shall be determined by a majority of the members of that group.
